      <div class="event-dot" style="top: 0;" tabindex="0" aria-controls="content1" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle 1979 - The Beginning at Lucasfilm details"></div>
      <h2 tabindex="0" aria-controls="content1" aria-expanded="false">1979 - The Beginning at Lucasfilm</h2>
      <div class="event-content" id="content1" aria-hidden="true">
        <p>Pixar's origins trace back to the Graphics Group, part of Lucasfilm's computer division, founded by Ed Catmull and Alvy Ray Smith. This team pioneered early computer graphics technology.</p>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Ed_Catmull_1.jpg/320px-Ed_Catmull_1.jpg" alt="Ed Catmull, co-founder of Pixar" class="event-image" />
        <blockquote>"Computers can do what people can’t — computers do stuff by rules, by math." - Ed Catmull</blockquote>
        <div class="trivia">Did you know? The team originally worked on developing digital editing systems before shifting focus to animation.</div>
        <p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ed_Catmull" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Learn more about Ed Catmull</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="event" id="event2">
      <div class="event-dot" style="top: 80px;" tabindex="0" aria-controls="content2" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle 1986 - Founding of Pixar details"></div>
      <h2 tabindex="0" aria-controls="content2" aria-expanded="false">1986 - Founding of Pixar</h2>
      <div class="event-content" id="content2" aria-hidden="true">
        <p>Steve Jobs acquires the Graphics Group from Lucasfilm, renaming it Pixar. It initially focuses on high-end graphics hardware, but gradually shifts towards animation software and content creation.</p>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Steve_Jobs_Headshot_2010-CROP2.jpg/320px-Steve_Jobs_Headshot_2010-CROP2.jpg" alt="Steve Jobs, co-founder of Pixar" class="event-image" />
        <blockquote>"Innovation distinguishes between a leader and a follower." - Steve Jobs</blockquote>
        <div class="trivia">Did you know? Steve Jobs invested $10 million to buy Pixar and believed in the potential of CGI animation early on.</div>
        <p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Jobs" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Learn more about Steve Jobs</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>

